BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the General Staff of the Armed Forces </F>
for the Liberation of Angola, UNITA, in Huambo on 6 June] 
  [Text] Jose Eduardo dos Santos' air force continues to 
launch attacks throughout Angola. 
  On 5 June, two Su-25's flying from Saurimo bombed (?Cuilo). 
Four bombs hit (Chicombe), killing 13 civilians, including 
traditional chief (Wangwa a Nona), and 25 civilians were 
seriously wounded. 
  On 6 June, Su-25's flying from the Catumbela Air Force 
dropped six bombs over Vila Nova, causing large-scale human and 
material losses. At least six people were killed and 29 wounded. 
  Those who sow the wind reap the whirlwind. 
  [Issued] Huambo, 6 June 1994 
  [Signed] Army General Ben Ben, chief of General Staff 

